# Jira Read-Only

This workflow has **read-only** access to Jira by default.

## Allowed

- Atlassian MCP read tools: `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql`, `getJiraIssue`, `getAccessibleAtlassianResources`, etc.
- GET requests to Jira REST / Agile APIs in custom scripts

## Forbidden (unless user explicitly requests write-back)

- `createJiraIssue`, `editJiraIssue`, `transitionJiraIssue`
- `addCommentToJiraIssue`, `addWorklogToJiraIssue`, `createIssueLink`
- POST / PUT / PATCH / DELETE to Jira endpoints

## If asked to update Jira

1. Refuse by default and cite this rule
2. Offer read-only alternative: local report with recommended due dates
3. Only proceed with writes if user explicitly overrides for a specific action
